. Before that, Alexander designed new finite-element mesh-generation methods, contributing to the PARMACS and PARASOL interfaces, and developed the first full MPI-2 and IMPI implementations in the world. He graduated from the Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology in 1990, and earned his PhD in applied mathematics at the Institute of Numerical Mathematics of the Russian Academy of Sciences in 1995. Alexander holds 26 patents (more pending worldwide).   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Okt 2018) 4aKeywords, Networking, Communications, Parallel computing, High performance computing, Point-to-point operations, Blocking operations, Supercomputing, OpenMPI.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2018 Englishz978311060402308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2018z9783110603118oZDB-23-DEI0 cEPUBz97815015067890 cprintz978150151554540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501506871423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501506871.jpg  aPDA5EBK  a978-3-11-060402-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DEIb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aPDA14ALL  aPDA1ALL